README

1. load CUDA module.
   You may want to specify the CUDA version for certain applications 
   after you get more familiar with the system.

 $module load CUDA

or depending on which cluster you're

 $module load cuda

2. compile the CUDA code you are working on. The default output is a.out

 $cd hello_world 
 $nvcc hello_world_device.cu

3. submit a job to run the CUDA code on a GUP node 

 $sbatch acer_cuda_run.sh

or

 $sbatch ncsa_cuda_run.sh

Good luck!
